The paper deals with developing a probabilistic model for predicting the behavior of robots based on percept-driven plans. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic inference methods, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the model to an autonomous robot office courier involves computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
